      "content": "i get the technical stuff, but honestly looking at the market, \"urban\" is almost always shorthand for Black or Latino street style. if i want to make sure my marketing and the actual look of the clothes don't feel \"off\" or like i'm mocking the community, should i be leaning into specific cultural tropes? like, are there certain ways certain groups express themselves through their clothes that i should be aware of so i don't mess it up?",
